The paper describes a graduate course that teaches practices for developing research software, which is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science. cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely category, as the course focuses on software development practices. cs.CE (Computational Engineering) is also likely, as the course is offered by an engineering program and the software development practices taught are applicable to engineering research. cs.PL (Programming Languages) is another possible category, as the course covers topics such as structuring Python modules and packaging and distribution. cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the course may be relevant to developing software for robotics research. cs.OH (Other Computer Science) is also a possibility, as the course may be applicable to a wide range of scientific research fields beyond engineering.
